4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): There is no direct connection to social or information networks in the paper, but the proposed model could potentially be used in the context of smart grids, which involve the integration of information and communication technologies with power systems. 5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with load forecasting, which is an important aspect of power system control. This makes cs.SY a possible sub-category.
